main event: A civilian observed unidentified objects with the appearance of glowing white and red tracers over California.
interesting points: The objects were observed through field glasses for around 50 minutes.
The objects appeared at intervals, without any formation.
The objects were observed at various altitudes, ranging from 3,000 feet to 38,000 feet.
The location of the sighting was near Fort Ord, California, and the cause was determined to be artillery firings from the base.
The report was filed as part of Project Blue Book, the U.S. Air Force's official program for investigating UFO sightings.
sighted object: Glowing white and red objects with the appearance of tracers
witnesses: A civilian woman, age 42, who was a deputy tax collector and treasurer of Santa Cruz
photographs: No photographs were included in the report
